### Análisis Antropológico: El Costo Cognitivo del Algoritmo (Burnout B2B)
* **Señal Técnica:** Radiografía de la fricción interna ("Espiral de disminución de engagement") que frena la distribución B2B y cómo la arquitectura algorítmica condiciona el 30% del esfuerzo mental de un líder de marketing.
* **Contenido Crudo:**
> Was gonna post about something, but first, I need to post about fear. The fear and neuroticism built by greed -- built by this #$%^ing algorithm to keep us all serving its quarterly numbers.
> 
> Works like this:
>  - I should promote that blog post/webinar/product/special/launch
>  - Ugh... what if it does poorly and tanks my engagement metrics?
>  - $%^# then I'll lose my shot at reaching more people with that thing I need to promote next week.
>  - What if that does poorly too? I'll get into a decreasing-engagement spiral. The algo will never show my posts to anyone again. I'll lose everything I've been building here.
>  - I'll skip it.
>  - But wait... if I don't post anything, my reach potential goes down too?! &^$%! Could AI?... No... Everyone's AI;DR now. Gotta come up with it myself.
>  - It's a damn trap! There's no winning.
> 
> Consciously or unconsciously, that's life on LinkedIn. Threads. Instagram. TikTok. YouTube. Every day the punishment for not posting is harsher. The competition stronger. The algo more ruthless in what it prunes and rewards. A good 30% of my day is spent thinking about what we could/should/will/won't put here. Exactly the way the social platforms want it.